                                                                                                                                    One more Taj hotel in Gulf

     OUR CORRESPONDENT
               
	Mumbai, Jan. 11: Taj Hotels, Resorts and Palaces today signed a management contract with Saraya Islands to develop a luxury resort in Ras Al Khaimah in the UAE. 
    
	The Indian Hotels Company and its subsidiaries are collectively known as Taj Hotels Resorts and Palaces. The Taj Exotica Resort and Spa in Ras Al Khaimah will come up around 2011.
    
	It will be a top end resort for the luxury traveller. Were also hoping to target markets such as Europe, North America, Russia and the Far East, said Ajoy Misra, senior vice-president of Indian Hotels Company (IHC). 
    
	While Taj Palace is already operational in Dubai, the Indian Hotels Company is setting up three more properties in the Gulf. Besides the Taj Exotica in Ras Al Khaimah, a Taj hotel is coming up in Doha and a Taj Exotica in Jumeirah, Palm Island.
    
	This alliance will open the door for many opportunities and is part of our strategy to build a global brand, said Raymond N. Bickson, managing director and CEO of IHC.
    
	Weve been quite active in expanding our global footprint for some time. Were constantly looking at opportunities as they come along, quot; Bickson added.
    
	Over the next 36 months, the IHC will develop 54 hotels, which will have 10,000 rooms. 
                                                                
